Is there a way for someone with an apple device to remove my watch from my account?

2025-08-11T14:23:44.606608Z assistant

Yes if you trust the person and they have an iPhone or iPad signed into your Apple ID, they can remove your watch from your account in just a couple minutes.

Heres the clean step-by-step youd give them:

If they have your watch in-hand

  1. Put the watch and iPhone close together.
  2. On the iPhone, open the Watch app.
  3. Tap All Watches (top left).
  4. Tap the next to your Ultra 2.
  5. Tap Unpair Apple Watch.
  6. Enter your Apple ID password when prompted.

If they dont have your watch in-hand (but they have your Apple ID and password)

  1. On their iPhone/iPad, sign into your Apple ID.
  2. Go to Find My app.
  3. Tap Devices, choose your Ultra 2.
  4. Tap Erase This Device Remove from Account.

Important: Theyll have full access to your Apple ID while signed in, so only do this with someone you fully trust and change your password immediately after.

How would they login to my apple id tho? Would it send a code in an email to allow the login?

2025-08-11T14:24:34.696205Z assistant

Yep Apple uses two-factor authentication for Apple ID logins, so heres what happens if someone tries to sign in on their device:

  1. They enter your Apple ID email and password.
  2. Apple immediately sends a 6-digit verification code to one of your trusted devices (iPhone, iPad, Mac) and to your Apple ID email.
  3. They have to enter that code on their device to complete the login.

Since you dont have an iPhone or other Apple device tied to the account, the verification code would come only through your Apple ID email (assuming thats still accessible to you).

So in your case:

  • They try to sign in.
  • You get the code via email.
  • You read/send them the code.
  • They finish logging in and remove the watch from your account.
  • You immediately change your password after theyre done.

Its totally doable it just means youll need live coordination for that 2FA step.
